//purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2953:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="attachment wp-att-699 lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A small-ish update fixing a bunch of things. Todays stats now show up correctly and AdRotate Pro now no longer nags you about W3 Total Cache when it shouldn&#8217;t. A bunch of output variables are now properly defined (and no longer show notices).</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[fix] Daily stats not always showing for some adverts</li>\n<li>[fix] Error about W3 Total Cache not being active while it is</li>\n<li>[fix] Undefined variable output</li>\n<li>[fix] Path to banner image (logo) in some notifications</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Morning Glory</h2>\n<p>Sewers are not always a luxury&#8230; Yes that stream is the sewer. And people live above it. Aside from whatever goes in a sewer, this one also was littered with garbage and plant debris. Combined with the 6 lane highway behind me it makes for a nice living environment&#8230; Right in the middle of Cebu City. Did I mention there&#8217;s a freight yard next door, too?</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-12808 lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer.jpg" alt="cebu-open-sewer" width="960" height="960" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-12808" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer-100x100.jpg 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer-300x300.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer-768x768.jpg 768w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer-200x200.jpg 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer-260x260.jpg 260w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer-380x380.jpg 380w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cebu-open-sewer.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></a></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s the Cebu City Port area for you. Highly commercialised and rife with industry. But also full of labourers living here.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"AdRotate 3.15  Better error checking";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://ajdg.solutions/2016/02/09/adrotate-3-15-better-error-checking/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 09 Feb 2016 13:28:55 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"AdRotate Plugin";s:7:"attri