ang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=11357";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:310:"It took a while to get right. Also the lack of feedback from a few people who were supposedly testing the beta slowed things down. But, things work for me. On both my test and real site. Yay and stuff. Widgets AdRotate Pro&#8217;s widget was kinda stale and dated &#8211; Requiring a manual ID entry. [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6123:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="attachment wp-att-699 lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>It took a while to get right. Also the lack of feedback from a few people who were supposedly testing the beta slowed things down. But, things work for me. On both my test and real site. Yay and stuff.</p>\n<h2>Widgets</h2>\n<p>AdRotate Pro&#8217;s widget was kinda stale and dated &#8211; Requiring a manual ID entry. I have created 2 easier to use widgets. Or I hope they&#8217;re easier to use. The widgets are simpler to control, one for adverts and one for groups.</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/adrotate-pro-widget.png" rel="attachment wp-att-11363 lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/adrotate-pro-widget.png" alt="adrotate-pro-widget" width="444" height="370" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11363" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/adrotate-pro-widget-300x250.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/adrotate-pro-widget.png 444w" sizes="(max-width: 444px) 100vw, 444px" /></a></p>\n<h2>Caching support</h2>\n<p>The implementation for W3 Total Cache has been updated to work. The current widget will not be updated for it. In a few months or so the old widget will go away entirely. The new widget uses the new implementation. Along with shortcode output, which has also been updated.</p>\n<p>If you want your widgets to work with W3 Total Caches fragmented caching you&#8217;ll want to switch over to the new widgets soon-ish. For shortcodes no action is required. The existing shortcodes have been updated.</p>\n<h2>Geo Targeting</h2>\n<p>AdRotate Pro now uses version 3 of my Geo API. This version is a bit faster and more efficient.<br />\nAlso here, no action required on your part. AdRotate Pro will automatically use the newer API.<br />\nThe API now handles in excess of 800000 requests per day. Quite a lot <img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> We&#8217;ll see how things hold up.</p>\n<h2>Post Injection</h2>\n<p>Once again, post injection has been updated. Stuffing multiple groups behind various paragraphs should now work more reliable. Meaning, adverts will actually show for more complex setups.</p>\n<p>Another new fancy thing is that Post Injection now finally works for widgets as well. You can set Post Injection to &#8216;Widget&#8217; now and then set up a group widget with that group. The widget will detect the post injection setting and act accordingly for pages and/or posts. Quite neat I think. This will work for both the standard Sidebar and other widget areas. The old widget does not support this feature. So using the new group widget is encouraged <img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<h2>Changelog</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[new] Post Injection extends to widgets</li>\n<li>[new] Page Injection extends to widgets</li>\n<li>[new] All new widgets for easier control and setup</li>\n<li>[new] AdRotate Geo API v3</li>\n<li>[new] AdRotate Update API v4</li>\n<li>[change] Dashboard tweaks</li>\n<li>[change] Better W3 Total Cache support</li>\n<li>[fix] Post injection not always showing with multiple groups</li>\n<li>[fix] Better day recognition for schedules</li>\n<li>[fix] Correct schedule creation for renewing adverts</li>\n<li>[fix] Correct device icons for adverts in groups and schedules</li>\n<li>[fix] Removed obsolete useragent column from database</li>\n<li>[fix] Better use of WP_Error for Geo Targeting</li>\n<li>[fix] Better error reporting for Geo Targeting</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Beta testing</h2>\n<p>In order to test a bunch of things I sent out beta versions to people willing to test. Once again it turned out a waste of time as nobody provided any feedback on things and just took the files and ran. Thanks for your assistance guys, really&#8230;<br />\nI probably won&#8217;t be providing beta&#8217;s again anytime soon <img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-includes/images/smilies/frownie.png" alt=":(" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<h2>I went into a cave!</h2>\n<p>I took a boat and went to this small rock island at the mound of Campomares Bay near Sipalay City. There was a big cave with tons of bats. Also one caveman was found&#8230; Red &#8216;Iron man&#8217; shirt, unwieldy beard. Claims he made AdRotate and thinks that makes him famous. Perhaps you&#8217;ve heard of him?</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/arnan-sipalay-cave.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-11364 lightbox-2"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/arnan-sipalay-cave-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="768" class="size-large wp-image-11364" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/arnan-sipalay-cave-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/arnan-sipalay-cave-768x576.jpg 768w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/arnan-sipalay-cave-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/arnan-sipalay-cave.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"Merchant E-Solutions payment gateway updated";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"https://ajdg.solutions/2016/01/16/merchant-e-solutions-payment-gateway-updated/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Jan 2016 16:46:58 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23:"Payment Gateway Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=11276";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:353:"A small update following up on the January 1 update. Version 1.1.1 has a clearer error message if your site can&#8217;t connect to the Merchant E-Solutions server or if some other kind of connection issue occurs. Changes Update The update is available via your dashboards regular update process for installations with a valid license. Paradise [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2232:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/merchant-esolutions.png" rel="attachment wp-att-3915 lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/merchant-esolutions-100x91.png" alt="merchant-esolutions" width="100" height="91" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-3915" /></a>A small update following up on the January 1 update. Version 1.1.1 has a clearer error message if your site can&#8217;t connect to the Merchant E-Solutions server or if some other kind of connection issue occurs.</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[fix] Better error response if gateway fails to connect</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated translation file</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Update</h2>\n<p>The update is available via your dashboards regular update process for installations with a valid license.</p>\n<h2>Paradise lost</h2>\n<p>Today in Sipalay, in the Philippines, I came across this tourism office. Perhaps useful to go there some time. But at the same time I wondered why it was there at all. This town has no tourism to speak of <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f609.png" alt="&#x1f609;" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> </p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-11278 lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office.jpg" alt="sipalay-tourism-office" width="960" height="960" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11278" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office-100x100.jpg 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office-300x300.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office-768x768.jpg 768w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office-200x200.jpg 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office-260x260.jpg 260w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office-380x380.jpg 380w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/sipalay-tourism-office.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"tit