ribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1546:"<p>Some updates for all payment gateway plugins. Mostly cosmetic stuff for now. Omnikassa will see some more internal improvements when I finally get around to it. Also for Merchant E-Solutions I have some ideas to make the plugin more feature rich without giving up usability.</p>\n<h2>Omnikassa for WooCommerce updated</h2>\n<p>A small but significant update for OmniCard. The name of the plugin is changing. First steps are included in this plugin. The plugin product page has had a make-over a while ago. OmniCard shall be known as <strong>Omnikassa for WooCommerce</strong>. Why change the name? It&#8217;s more fitting after-all. I&#8217;ve also updated the footer links in the plugin accordingly. Remnants of the OmniCard name will be removed over the coming updates but are more complex than a cosmetic change. This update has the cosmetic stuff <img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<p>Updates are available now from your account on this website or via the automated updater.</p>\n<h2>Merchant E-Solutions</h2>\n<p>WooCommerce Merchant E-Solutions got an update a few days ago. Fixing a response error but also updating the footer links to reflect a more current approach for my sites and direction.<br />\nThe dashboard got redone as well, with much better controls for testing.</p>\n<p>Also for WooCommerce Merchant E-Solutions, updates are available now via the automated update system and via your account on this website.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explici