"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:350:"After a few days of testing the plugin appears ready for live use again. For some users the responses of the Merchant E-Solutions server were processed wrong resulting in orders being paid and WooCommerce not knowing about it. I&#8217;ve worked with a few users and the Merchant E-Solutions certification team to resolve this issue. Earlier [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3169:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/merchant-esolutions.png" rel="attachment wp-att-3915 lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/merchant-esolutions.png" alt="merchant-esolutions" width="200" height="91" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-3915" /></a>After a few days of testing the plugin appears ready for live use again. For some users the responses of the Merchant E-Solutions server were processed wrong resulting in orders being paid and WooCommerce not knowing about it. I&#8217;ve worked with a few users and the Merchant E-Solutions certification team to resolve this issue.</p>\n<p>Earlier today Merchant E-Solutions sort of gave the go ahead noting that all transaction requests are sent out perfectly and on my end I verified that they are processed correctly so your order statuses are correct too.</p>\n<h2>Pre-Auth / Settlements</h2>\n<p>During these tests I&#8217;ve also experimented a bit with Pre-authorized payments. While the concept for this is nothing special. WooCommerce makes it very hard to implement. I don&#8217;t fully understand the mechanics in WooCommerce for it. Nor does any of the relevant triggers for the settlement claim seem to work&#8230; Something to explore for a later date. But certainly not forgotten <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f609.png" alt="&#x1f609;" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<h2>Settings</h2>\n<p>During testing it became apparent that the dashboard and checkout options were insufficient for quick testing which made the whole process tedious and stupid. I have revised the settings dashboard in WooCommerce > Settings > Checkout to be more easy in use as well as adding test datas on checkout for you to use when making test transactions. Check out the new settings dashboard and verify your stuff is still up-to-date.</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[new] Much improved settings and testing options</li>\n<li>[change] All new dashboard settings page</li>\n<li>[fix] Order response not always processing properly</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated translation file</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Rice farming on Guimaras Island</h2>\n<p>Your rice may be grown by this farmer. This is his house. Right in the middle of a bunch of rice paddies. Surely there was no farming equipment in sight. No machines, or even a cow. Just hardcore farming going on here.</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/guimaras-farmhouse.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-10771 lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/guimaras-farmhouse-1024x768.jpg" alt="guimaras-farmhouse" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-10771" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/guimaras-farmhouse-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/guimaras-farmhouse-768x576.jpg 768w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/guimaras-farmhouse-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/guimaras-farmhouse.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"